OL,3,CGrandmother diagnosed with blood
OL,4,Cdisease she didn't know she had after
OL,5,Cnew test
OL,7,FShe said: "I'm glad that it's been
OL,8,Ffound. I've had scans, I've had blood
OL,9,Ftests. They're going to monitor me.
OL,11,F"I am reassured. If I didn't have that
OL,12,Fpain that night - I wouldn't have
OL,13,Fknown about this and I would have
OL,14,Fcarried on regardless. "
OL,16,FThe groundbreaking opt-out testing
OL,17,Fprogramme in Birmingham's hospital
OL,18,Femergency departments has already led
OL,19,Fto over 36 new diagnoses of blood-
OL,20,Fborne viruses (BBVs), including HIV,
OL,21,Fhepatitis B, and hepatitis C.
